ay|100 m relay - T11-13]]}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Asian Para Games]]}}\n{{MedalSilver|[[2010 Asian Para Games|2010 Guangzhou]]|[[Athletics at the 2010 Asian Para Games|100 m - T11]]}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[IPC Athletics Asia-Oceania Championship|Asia-Oceania Championships]]}}\n{{MedalGold|[[IPC Athletics Asia-Oceania Championship 2016|2016 Dubai]]|[[IPC Athletic Asia-Oceania Championship 2016 \u2013 Women's 100 metres|100 m - T11]]}}\n{{MedalGold|[[IPC Athletics Asia-Oceania Championship 2016|2016 Dubai]]|[[IPC Athletic Asia-Oceania Championship 2016 \u2013 Women's 200 metres|200 m - T11]]}}\n}}\n\n'''Jia Juntingxian''' (born 17 August 1986) is a visually impaired [[Paralympian]] [[Track and field|athlete]] from [[China]] competing mainly in [[T11 (classification)|T11 classification]] sprint and [[long jump]] events.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.paralympic.org/static/info/doha-2015/ENG/ZB/ZBB101A_QA2015AT@@@@@@@ENG_number=12104.htm|title=Jia Juntingxian|accessdate=21 August 2016|work=paralympic.org}}</ref> Zhou won two medals at her first Summer Paralympics, the [[2012 Summer Paralympics|2012 London Games]], in the women's 200m sprint (bronze) and the long jump (silver). Jia is also a World Championships and Asian Games medalists, winning seven medals over five tournaments.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.paralympic.org/asp/lib/theasp.asp?pageid=8937&sportid=513&personid=903958&refreshauto=1|title=Jia Juntingxian|accessdate=21 August 2016|work=[[International Paralympic Committee|IPC]]}}</ref>\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.paralympic.org/ipc_results/search.php?sport=all&games=all&medal=all&npc=all&gender=all&name=Jia&fname=Juntingxian Jia Juntingxian at the International Paralympic Committee]{{dead link|date=July 2017}}\n* {{IPC athlete|903958}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Jia, Juntingxian}}\n[[Category:1986 births]]\n[[Category:Chinese female sprinters]]\n[[Category:Chinese female long jumpers]]\n[[Category:Paralympic athletes of China]]\n[[Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2012 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2016 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Paralympic gold medalists for China]]\n[[Category:Paralympic bronze medalists for China]]\n[[Category:Paralympic silver medalists for China]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 2012 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 2016 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Runners from Jiangxi]]\n\n\n{{PRChina-athletics-bio-stub}}\n{{PRChina-Paralympic-medalist-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Zyxw", "label": "safe", "comment": "update IPC external link", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jia_Juntingxian"}
{"title_page": "Idris Elba", "text_new": "{{short description|English actor, producer, DJ, rapper, and singer}}\n{{pp-semi-blp|small=yes}}\n{{Use British English|date=August 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Idris Elba\n| honorific_suffix   = {{post-nominals|country=GBR|size=100%|OBE}}\n| image              = File:Idris Elba-5272.jpg\n| caption            = Elba in February 2018\n| birth_name         = Idrissa Akuna Elba\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1972|9|06}}\n| birth_place        = [[London Borough of Hackney|Hackney, London]], England\n| citizenship = British<br>Sierra Leonean (since 2019)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-50871307|title=Idris Elba given Sierra Leone citizenship|date=20 December 2019|via=www.bbc.com}}</ref>\n| othername          = {{hlist|DJ Big Driis|Big Driis the Londoner|Big Driis|7 Dub|Me Innit<ref>{{cite news |first= Jada |last=Yuan |title=Idris Elba on Prometheus, Learning to Box, and His Party House |url=http://www.vulture.com/2012/06/idris-elba-prometheus-interview.html |accessdate=14 October 2013 |newspaper=vulture.com |date=8 June 2012}}</ref>}}\n| occupation         ={{flatlist|\n* Actor\n* writer\n* producer\n* DJ\n* rapper\n* singer}}\n| yearsactive        = 1994\u2013present\n| spouse = {{marriage|Hanne N\u00f8rgaard|1999|2003|end=divorced}}<br>{{marriage|Sonya Nicole Hamlin<br>|2006|2006|end=[[Annulment|{{abbr|annul.|annulled}}]]}}<br/> {{marriage|Sabrina Dhowre<br>|2019}}\n| partner = Naiyana Garth (2013\u20132016)\n| children           = 2\n| awards = [[List of awards and nominations received by Idris Elba|List of awards and nominations]]\n| module = {{infobox musical artist\n| embed = yes\n| background = solo_singer\n| genre = {{hlist|[[Hip hop music|Hip hop]]|[[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]}}\n| instruments = {{hlist|Vocals|[[turntablist|turntables]]}}\n| label = [[Parlophone Records|Parlophone]], 7Wallace}}\n}}\n\n'''Idrissa Akuna Elba''' {{post-nominals|country=GBR|size=100%|OBE}} ({{IPAc-en|\u02c8|\u026a|d|r|\u026a|s}}; born 6 September 1972) is an <!----Do not change this to \"British\" without obtaining consensus to do so on the talk page first, otherwise it will just be reverted back--\nThe cited article quotes him calling himself \"English\"-->English<!----per Elba quote from Esquire interview; \"So I said, 'Listen guys, I'm English.\"----> actor, writer, producer, musician, and DJ.<ref>[http://www.esquire.co.uk/culture/news/a5110/idris-elba-interview-the-hustler/ \"Idris Elba Interview: The Hustler\"]. Esquire. Retrieved 18 April 2016</ref> He is known for roles including [[Stringer Bell]] in the [[HBO]] series ''[[The Wire]]'',<ref name=\"hbo\">{{cite web|title=The Wire Cast and Crew: Idris Elba, Russell 'Stringer' Bell |publisher=HBO.com |url=http://www.hbo.com/thewire/cast/actors/idris_elba.shtml |accessdate=11 April 2009}}</ref> [[Chief inspector#United Kingdom|DCI]] [[John Luther]] in the [[BBC One]] series ''[[Luther (TV series)|Luther]]'', and [[Nelson Mandela]] in the biographical film ''[[Mandela: Long Walk to Freedom]]'' (2013). He has been nominated four times for a [[Golden Globe Award for Best Actor \u2013 Miniseries or Television Film]], winning one, and was nominated five times for a [[Primetime Emmy Award]].<ref>{{cite journal|first=Brian |last=Lowry |url=https://variety.com/2014/tv/news/emmy-nominations-2014-list-emmys-nominees-1201260236/ |title=Emmy Nominations 2014 \u2014 Full List: 66th Primetime Emmys Nominees |journal=Variety |date=10 July 2014 |accessdate=28 January 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"Luther\">{{cite news |title=Wire actor Elba joins BBC drama |work=BBC News |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/8237924.stm |accessdate=7 September 2009 |date=4 September 2009}}</ref>\n\nElba appeared in [[Ridley Scott]]'s ''[[American Gangster (film)|American Gangster]]'' (2007) and ''[[Prometheus (2012 film)|Prometheus]]'' (2012). Elba portrayed [[Heimdall (comics)|Heimdall]] in ''[[Thor (film)|Thor]]'' (2011) and its sequels ''[[Thor: The Dark World]]'' (2013) and ''[[Thor: Ragnarok]]'' (2017), as well as ''[[Avengers: Age of Ultron]]'' (2015) and ''[[Avengers: Infinity War]]'' (2018). He also starred in ''[[Pacific Rim (film)|Pacific Rim]]'' (2013), ''[[Beasts of No Nation (film)|Beasts of No Nation]]'' (2015), for which he received [[BAFTA Award for Best Actor in a Supporting Role|BAFTA]] and [[Golden Globe Award for Best Supporting Actor \u2013 Motion Picture|Golden Globe]] nominations for Best Supporting Actor, and ''[[Molly's Game]]'' (2017). In 2016, he voiced Chief Bogo in ''[[Zootopia]]'', [[Shere Khan]] in the live action/CGI adaptation of ''[[The Jungle Book (2016 film)|The Jungle Book]]'', Fluke in ''[[Finding Dory]]'', and played the role of Krall in ''[[Star Trek Beyond]]''. He made his directorial debut in 2018 with [[Yardie (film)|an adaptation]] of the 1992 novel ''[[Yardie (novel)|Yardie]]'' by [[Victor Headley]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://collider.com/idris-elba-yardie-director/ |title=Idris Elba Set to Make Directorial Debut With ''Yardie'' |last=Cabin |first=Chris |website=[[Collider (website)|Collider]] |date=5 July 2016 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6imkfzpT4?url=http://collider.com/idris-elba-yardie-director/ |archivedate=5 July 2016 |url-status=live |accessdate=5 July 2016  }}</ref>\n\nIn addition to his acting work, Elba performs as a DJ under the moniker '''DJ Big Driis''' (or '''Big Driis the Londoner''') and as an [[R&B]] musician.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://hiphopwired.com/2011/09/13/idris-elba-driis-releases-new-music-video-secret-garden-video/ |title=Idris Elba (Driis) Releases New Music Video 'Secret Garden' |date=13 September 2011 |publisher=hiphopwired.com |first=Danielle |last=Canada}}</ref> In 2016, he was named in the [[Time 100|''Time'' 100]] list of the Most Influential People in the World.<ref>{{cite news |author=David Simon|url=http://time.com/4299764/idris-elba-2016-time-100//|title=Idris Elba: TIME 100|work=TIME.com|accessdate=27 April 2016}}</ref> As of May 2019, his films have grossed over {{US$|9.8 billion|long=no}} at the global box office, including over {{US$|3.6 billion|long=no}} in North America,<ref>{{cite web |title=Idris Elba Movie Box Office Results |url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/people/chart/?view=Actor&id=idriselba.htm |website=[[Box Office Mojo]] |accessdate=6 May 2019}}</ref> where he is one of the top 20 highest-grossing actors.<ref>{{cite web |title=People Index {{ndash}} Actors: Total Gross |url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/people/?view=Actor&sort=sumgross&p=.htm |website=[[Box Office Mojo]] |accessdate=6 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nElba was born on 6 September 1972<ref name=\"guardian\"/> at Forest Gate Hospital in [[London Borough of Hackney|Hackney, London]],<ref name=Biography.com>{{cite web|url=https://www.biography.com/people/idris-elba-21429871| title= Idris Elba:Singer, Actor (1972\u2013)|publisher=[[Biography.com]] ([[FYI (TV network)|FYI]] / [[A&E Networks]])| accessdate=2 August 2017|quote=Idrissa Akuna Elba was born on September 6, 1972, in the Hackney section of East London, England. An only child of Sierra Leonean descent, Elba eventually attended the National Youth Music Theatre's training programs.}}</ref> the son of Winston, a [[Sierra Leonean]] man who worked at the [[Ford Dagenham]] plant, and Eve, a [[Ghanaian people|Ghanaian]] woman.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/film/beasts-of-no-nation/cary-fukunaga-interview/|title=Idris Elba meets his Waterloo \u2013 in Ghana|date=3 October 2015|work=The Telegraph|accessdate=23 November 2018|issn=0307-1235}}</ref> Elba's parents were married in Sierra Leone and later moved to London.<ref name=\"observer_2010\">{{cite web |url= https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2010/jan/24/idris-elba-interview-the-wire |title=Idris Elba: life after 'Stringer' Bell |first=Miranda |last=Sawyer|authorlink=Miranda Sawyer |work=[[The Observer]] |date=24 January 2010 |accessdate=28 January 2015}}</ref> Elba was raised up in Hackney and [[East Ham]],<ref name=\"Midas Touch\">{{cite news|first=Stuart |last=Jeffries |date=9 May 2009|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2009/may/05/television-the-wire-idris-elba-obsessed |title=The Midas Touch |work=The Guardian |accessdate=29 July 2009|location=London}}</ref> and shortened his first name to \"Idris\" at school in [[Canning Town]], where he first became involved in acting. He credits ''[[The Stage]]'' with giving him his first big break, having seen an advertisement for a play in it; he auditioned and met his first agent while performing in the role.<ref name=\"baftaguru_2013\">{{cite web |url= http://guru.bafta.org/idris-elba-big-questions |title=Idris Elba: Big Questions |work=[[BAFTA|BAFTA Guru]] |date=19 June 2013 |accessdate=17 August 2015}}</ref> In 1986, he began helping an uncle with his wedding DJ business; within a year, he had started his own DJ company with some of his friends.<ref name=\"guardian\"/> Elba left school in 1988, and won a place in the [[National Youth Music Theatre]] thanks to a \u00a31,500 [[The Prince's Trust|Prince's Trust]] grant.<ref>[https://www.princeofwales.gov.uk/news-and-diary/princes-trust-celebrate-success \"Prince's Trust Celebrate Success\"]. Prince of Wales.gov.uk. Retrieved 2 December 2017</ref> To support himself between roles in his early career, he worked in odd jobs including: tyre-fitting, [[cold-calling]], and night shifts at Ford Dagenham.<ref name=\"times\">{{cite news|first=Chris |last=Ayres |date=23 August 2008 | url = http://entertainment.timesonline.co.uk/tol/arts_and_entertainment/film/article4572201.ece | title=Life as a RocknRolla: meet the crafty Cockney Idris Elba |work=The Times |accessdate=11 April 2009|location=London}}</ref> He was working in nightclubs under the DJ nickname \"Big Driis\" during his adolescence, but began auditioning for television roles in his early twenties.<ref name=\"guardian\"/>\n\n==Acting career==\n===Television===\nElba's first acting role was in ''[[Crimewatch]]'' murder reconstructions and in 1994 he appeared in a BBC children's drama called ''The Boot Street Band''. In 1995, he landed his first significant role on a series called ''[[Bramwell (TV series)|Bramwell]]'', a medical drama set in 1890s England. He played a central character in an episode of Season 1, an African petty thief named Charlie Carter, who lost his (white) wife to childbirth and had to figure out how to support his newborn daughter. His first named role arrived earlier in 1995, when he was cast as a [[gigolo]] on the \"Sex\" episode of ''[[Absolutely Fabulous]]''. Many supporting roles on British television followed, including series such as ''[[The Bill]]'' and ''[[The Ruth Rendell Mysteries]]''. He joined the cast of the soap opera ''[[Family Affairs]]''<ref name=\"guardian\">{{cite news|first=Esther |last=Addley |date=20 March 2008 |url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2008/mar/21/television |title=He often has fewer lines than anyone else but you still feel as though he has the bigger part, because he is luminous |work=The Guardian |accessdate=23 August 2013| archivedate= 1 December 2016| archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20161201214845/https://www.theguardian.com/media/2008/mar/21/television| url-status=live}}</ref> and went on to appear on the television serial ''[[Ultraviolet (TV serial)|Ultraviolet]]'' and later on ''[[Dangerfield (TV series)|Dangerfield]]''.<ref>{{cite web |title=Idris Elba \u2013 Biography|url=https://movies.yahoo.com/person/idris-elba/biography.html |publisher=[[Yahoo! Movies]]|accessdate=17 July 2013}}</ref> He decided to move to New York City soon after.<ref name=\"guardian\"/> He returned to England occasionally for a television role, such as a part in one of the ''[[Inspector Lynley Mysteries]]''. In 2001, Elba played Achilles in a stage production of ''[[Troilus and Cressida]]'' in New York City.<ref name=\"guardian\"/>\n\nAfter a supporting turn on a 2001 episode of ''[[Law & Order]]'', Elba landed a starring role on the 2002 HBO drama series ''The Wire''. From 2002 to 2004, Elba portrayed Russell \"Stringer\" Bell in the series, perhaps his best-known role in the United States. In 2005, he portrayed [[Captain (armed forces)|Captain]] Augustin Muganza in ''[[Sometimes in April]]'', an HBO film about the [[Rwandan genocide]]. Elba appeared on the 2007 [[BET]] special ''Black Men: The Truth''.<ref>{{cite web |title=Idris Elba |url=http://uk.askmen.com/celebs/men/entertainment/idris-elba/ |work=askmen.com |accessdate=17 July 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130807231102/http://uk.askmen.com/celebs/men/entertainment/idris-elba/ |archivedate=7 August 2013  }}</ref> He appeared as Charlie Gotso on ''[[The No. 1 Ladies' Detective Agency (TV series)|The No. 1 Ladies' Detective Agency]]'', filmed in [[Botswana]].<ref name=\"variety\">{{cite news|title='Detective Agency' finds big auds |work=Variety |url=http://www.variety.com/article/VR1117982869.html?categoryid=14&cs=1 |accessdate=11 April 2009 |first=Archie |last=Thomas |date=25 March 2008}}</ref> The series premiered on 23 March 2008, Easter Sunday, on BBC One, receiving a high 6.3 million viewers and 27% of the audience share.<ref>{{cite news |title=Minghella's last film watched by 6.3m |work=The Guardian |url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2008/mar/25/tvratings.television |accessdate=11 April 2009 |location=London |first=John |last=Plunkett |date=25 March 2008}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2009, it was reported by ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' that Elba would portray [[List of The Office (U.S. TV series) characters#Charles Miner|Charles Miner]], a new rival to Dunder Mifflin regional manager Michael Scott ([[Steve Carell]]) for [[NBC]]'s ''[[The Office (U.S. TV series)|The Office]]''.<ref name=\"variety\"/> Elba appeared in a six-episode story arc later in the 2009 season as well as the season finale.<ref name=\"variety\"/>\nIn September 2009, he signed a deal to star as the lead role on the six-part BBC television series ''[[Luther (TV series)|Luther]]'', which aired in May 2010.<ref name=\"Luther\"/> He appeared on [[Showtime (TV network)|Showtime's]] ''[[The Big C (TV series)|The Big C]]'' in 2010.<ref name=\"Deadline\">{{cite web |title=Idris Elba Is New Alex Cross in Relaunched James Patterson Film Franchise |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=18 August 2010 |url=http://www.deadline.com/2010/08/idris-elba-is-new-alex-cross-in-relaunched-james-patterson-film-franchise |accessdate=19 August 2010}}</ref> At the [[69th Golden Globe Awards]] telecast on 15 January 2012, Elba won the Award for Best Actor in a Series, Mini-Series, or Motion Picture Made for Television for his role on the BBC crime thriller series ''Luther''.<ref name=\"Luther\"/>\n\nIn April 2018, it was announced that Elba was cast as Charlie in the [[Netflix]] comedy series, ''[[Turn Up Charlie]]''.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Otterson|first1=Joe|title=Idris Elba to Star in Netflix Comedy Series 'Turn Up Charlie'|url=https://variety.com/2018/tv/news/idris-elba-netflix-comedy-series-turn-up-charlie-1202756227/|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|accessdate=21 February 2019|date=18 April 2018}}</ref> He also created and starred in the semi-autobiographical comedy ''In The Long Run''.<ref>{{cite news |last= Sturges |first= Fiona |date= 24 March 2018 |title= In the Long Run: Idris Elba's joyful portrait of community in 1980s Hackney |url= https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2018/mar/24/idris-elba-in-the-long-run |newspaper= [[The Guardian]] |accessdate= 4 April 2019 }}</ref>\n\n===Film===\n[[File:RockNRolla08TIFF.jpg|thumb|Elba (''back row, centre'') with the cast of ''[[RocknRolla]]'' at the 2008 [[Toronto International Film Festival]]]]\nIn 2007, Elba signed on as the lead role of the film ''[[Daddy's Little Girls]]'', playing Monty, a blue-collar mechanic who falls in love with an attorney helping him gain custody of his kids, and finds the relationship and his custody hopes threatened by the return of his former wife. He appeared in ''[[28 Weeks Later]]'' (2007) and ''[[This Christmas (film)|This Christmas]]'' (2007), which brought in nearly $50 million at the box office in 2007.<ref name=\"moviesonline\">{{cite web|title=Idris Elba and Columbus Short Interview, This Christmas |publisher=Moviesonline.ca |url=http://www.moviesonline.ca/movienews_13494.html |accessdate=11 April 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150114063242/http://www.moviesonline.ca/movienews_13494.html |archivedate=14 January 2015  }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=This Christmas|publisher=Thenumbers.com|url=http://www.the-numbers.com/movies/2007/TCHRS.php|accessdate=11 April 2009}}</ref> In 2008, he starred in the horror film ''[[Prom Night (2008 film)|Prom Night]]'' and the [[Guy Ritchie]] London gangster film ''[[RocknRolla]]''.<ref name=\"moviesonline\"/> In 2009, he starred in the horror film ''[[The Unborn (2009 film)|The Unborn]]'' and in ''[[Obsessed (2009 film)|Obsessed]]'', a thriller that had him cast opposite [[Beyonc\u00e9]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Idris Elba And Beyonce To Play Married Couple In 'Obsessed'| publisher =Blackvoices.com|url=http://www.blackvoices.com/blogs/2008/03/06/idris-elba-and-beyonce-to-play-married-couple-in-obsessed/|accessdate=11 April 2009}}</ref> The latter was a box office success, taking $29 million in its opening weekend.<ref>{{cite web|title=Weekend Report: Moviegoers Fixate on 'Obsessed'|publisher=Boxofficemojo.com|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/news/?id=2581&p=.htm|accessdate=26 April 2009}}</ref>\n\nElba's next film was ''[[Legacy (2010 film)|Legacy]]'' (2010),<ref name=\"UKPA\">{{cite web|date=8 July 2009|url=https://www.google.com/hostednews/ukpress/article/ALeqM5h_xUEDxNYFY1a0hUDXk---CCuTwQ|title=Idris Elba gets his kit off on set|work=UKPA|accessdate=21 July 2009}}</ref> in which he portrayed a [[black ops]] soldier who returns to Brooklyn after a failed mission in Eastern Europe, where he has undertaken a journey looking for retribution.<ref name=\"UKPA\"/> He starred in [[Dark Castle]]'s adaptation of [[DC Comics|DC]]/[[Vertigo (DC Comics)|Vertigo's]] ''[[The Losers (Vertigo)|The Losers]]'', under the direction of [[Sylvain White]], in the role of Roque, the second-in-command of a black-ops team out for revenge against a government that did them wrong.<ref>{{cite web|title=Idris Elba Confirmed For 'The Losers,' Zoe Saldana Playing Aisha|author=Josh Wigler|publisher=MTV|url=http://splashpage.mtv.com/2009/04/02/idris-elba-confirmed-for-the-losers-zoe-saldana-playing-aisha|date=2 April 2009|accessdate=11 April 2009|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090405194051/http://splashpage.mtv.com/2009/04/02/idris-elba-confirmed-for-the-losers-zoe-saldana-playing-aisha|archivedate=5 April 2009}}</ref> Filming took place in [[Puerto Rico]] and the movie was released in April 2010.<ref name=\"Business Wire\">{{cite web|date=29 July 2009|url=http://www.businesswire.com/portal/site/google/?ndmViewId=news_view&newsId=20090729006447&newsLang=en|title=\"The Losers\" Commences Production for Dark Castle Entertainment|work=[[Business Wire]]|accessdate=5 August 2009}}</ref> Elba appeared in the thriller ''Takers'' (2010). He played [[Heimdall (comics)|Heimdall]] in [[Kenneth Branagh]]'s film ''Thor'' (2011) (based on the [[Marvel Comics]] [[Thor (Marvel Comics)|superhero of the same name]]).<ref name=\"elba\">{{cite news|url=http://www.heatvisionblog.com/2009/11/idris-elba-joins-marvel-studios-thor-natalie-portman-kenneth-branagh.html|title=Idris Elba joins Marvel Studios' 'Thor'|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=20 November 2009|accessdate=20 November 2009}}</ref>\n\nIn August 2010, Elba signed up to portray the title character in a reboot of [[James Patterson]]'s [[Alex Cross]] film franchise.<ref name=\"Deadline\"/> However, in February 2011, he was replaced by [[Tyler Perry]].<ref name = \"perryin_elbaout\">{{cite news|url=http://www.ew.com/article/2011/02/01/tyler-perry-alex-cross-idris-elba|title=Tyler Perry in, Idris Elba out of Alex Cross reboot: Producer explains why \u2013 EXCLUSIVE|last=Bierly |first=Mandi |date=1 February 2011 |work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|accessdate=18 September 2011}}</ref> In ''[[Ghost Rider: Spirit of Vengeance]]'' (2011), the sequel to ''[[Ghost Rider (2007 film)|Ghost Rider]]'' (2007), Elba played an alcoholic warrior monk tasked with finding the title character.<ref name=\"elbaandwhitworth\">{{cite news|url=http://heatvision.hollywoodreporter.com/2010/10/ghost-rider-2-nicolas-cage-idris-elba-johnny-whitworth.html|title=Idris Elba, Johnny Whitworth gear up for 'Ghost Rider 2'|work=The Hollywood Reporter|first=Boris |last= Kit|date=5 October 2010|accessdate=6 October 2010}}</ref> In February 2012, Elba confirmed that he would portray Nelson Mandela in the film ''Mandela: Long Walk to Freedom'', which is based on his [[Long Walk to Freedom|autobiography]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/02/22/idris-elba-mandela_n_1295010.html|title=Confirmed! Idris Elba set to play Nelson Mandela in Biopic|work=Huffington Post|accessdate=23 February 2012|first=Lucette|last=Jefferson|date=22 February 2012}}</ref> As part of his preparation for the role, Elba spent a night locked in a cell alone on [[Robben Island]], where Mandela had been imprisoned.<ref>{{cite journal|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/12/07/idris-elba-nelson-mandela_n_4400768.html |title=Idris Elba Describes Chilling Night In Nelson Mandela's Prison (VIDEO) |journal=[[Huffington Post]] |date=7 December 2013 |accessdate=28 January 2015}}</ref> His performance earned him a nomination for the [[Golden Globe Award for Best Actor \u2013 Motion Picture Drama]].\n\nIn June 2012, Elba portrayed Captain Janek in Ridley Scott's ''Prometheus''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ifc.com/2012/09/prometheus-video-idris-elba|title=Prometheus video teases more from Idris Elba's Captain Janek|publisher=ifc.com|date=September 2012|accessdate=13 April 2016}}</ref> He joined the cast of the film ''Pacific Rim'' (2013) in the role of Stacker Pentecost.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blogs.indiewire.com/shadowandact/archives/its_official_idris_elba_will_star_in_guillermo_del_toros_pacific_rim_bla|title=It's Official! Idris Elba Will Star in Guillermo del Toro's \"Pacific Rim\" (Black Superhero Next?)|publisher=Blogs.indiewire.com|accessdate=28 December 2011|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120710105832/http://blogs.indiewire.com/shadowandact/archives/its_official_idris_elba_will_star_in_guillermo_del_toros_pacific_rim_bla|archivedate=10 July 2012}}</ref> He reprised his role as [[Heimdall]] in ''[[Thor: The Dark World]]'' in 2013. In January 2014, he confirmed that he would be starring in a film adaptation of ''Luther''.<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/tv/tv-news/mandelas-idris-elba-confirms-luther-2984600 |title=Mandela actor Idris Elba confirms Luther film |work=The Mirror |date=3 January 2014}}</ref> In 2014, he starred in ''[[No Good Deed (2014 film)|No Good Deed]]'' as a vengeful psychopathic serial killer.\n\nIn 2015, Elba appeared as Heimdall in the superhero blockbuster ''[[Avengers: Age of Ultron]]'', directed by [[Joss Whedon]]. Elba also starred alongside [[Abraham Attah]] in the film ''[[Beasts of No Nation (film)|Beasts of No Nation]]'' which premiered in select theaters and on [[Netflix]]. He earned a [[Golden Globe Award]] nomination for Best Performance by an Actor in a Supporting Role in any Motion Picture as well as a [[BAFTA Award]] nomination for Supporting Actor in the Film category. In 2016, he had several voice roles: the cape buffalo chief of police, Chief Bogo, in Disney's ''Zootopia'', alongside [[Ginnifer Goodwin]] and [[Jason Bateman]]; villainous tiger [[Shere Khan]] in ''[[The Jungle Book (2016 film)|The Jungle Book]]'' (2016), a live-action adaptation of [[The Jungle Book (1967 film)|the animated 1967 film of the same name]], directed by [[Jon Favreau]]; and sea lion Fluke in [[Pixar]]'s ''[[Finding Dory]]'', alongside [[Ellen DeGeneres]] and [[Albert Brooks]], both reprising their roles from ''[[Finding Nemo]]'' (2003). Also that year, he played the main antagonist, Krall, in the sequel ''[[Star Trek Beyond]]''. In 2017, he played [[Roland Deschain]] in the Stephen King film adaptation ''[[The Dark Tower (2017 film)|The Dark Tower]]'',<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.ew.com/article/2016/02/29/dark-tower-rises-stephen-king-idris-elba-and-matthew-mcconaughey|title='The Dark Tower' rises: Stephen King confirms stars Idris Elba and Matthew McConaughey|magazine=Entertainment Weekly}}</ref> and starred in [[Aaron Sorkin]]'s [[directorial debut]] ''Molly's Game'', alongside [[Jessica Chastain]]. In 2019, Elba starred as the villain in ''[[Hobbs & Shaw|Fast & Furious Presents: Hobbs & Shaw]]'', a spin-off of ''[[Fast & Furious]]'' franchise, and played Macavity in [[Tom Hooper]]'s [[Cats (2019 film)|film adaptation]] of [[Andrew Lloyd Webber]]\u2019s musical, ''[[Cats (musical)|Cats]]''.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://ew.com/movies/2018/10/16/idris-elba-joins-cats-movie/|title=Idris Elba to join Ian McKellen, Taylor Swift in Cats movie adaptation|magazine=Entertainment Weekly}}</ref>\n\n==Music career==\n[[File:Idris Elba 2007 Cropped.jpg|thumb|upright|Elba at the [[American Music Awards]] in 2007]]\nElba has appeared in music videos for [[Fat Joe]] (2002),<ref>{{youtube|QE36OI8Za6o|Fat Joe \u2013 All I Need}}</ref> [[Angie Stone]] (2004)<ref>{{youtube|W5ZUTTQHOfM|Angie Stone \u2013 I Wanna Thank Ya}}</ref> and rapper [[Giggs (rapper)|Giggs]] (2010).<ref>{{youtube|K8_XbEmQHNM|Giggs \u2013 Hustle on official video}}</ref> In 2006, he recorded the four-song [[Extended play|EP]] ''Big Man'' for Hevlar Records. He co-produced and performed on the intro to [[Jay-Z]]'s album ''[[American Gangster (album)|American Gangster]]'' (2007).<ref>{{cite web|title=He often has fewer lines than anyone else but you still feel as though he has the bigger part, because he is luminous|publisher=Movietome.com|url=http://www.movietome.com/pages/tracking/index.php?sls_id=30960|accessdate=11 April 2009}}{{dead link|date=November 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> He DJed at the 2007 [[NBA]] All Star parties at [[The Venetian Las Vegas|The Venetian]] and Ice House Lounge in [[Las Vegas]].<ref name=\"Ties\">{{cite news|first=John |last=McMurtrie|date=11 February 2007|url=http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?f=/c/a/2007/02/11/PKG4MNV3NJ1.DTL&hw=Elba&sn=001&sc=1000|title=Ties to 'Wire' cut \u2013 but new work calls|work=San Francisco Chronicle|accessdate=11 April 2009}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2009, Elba was the DJ for [[Black Entertainment Television|BET's]] current series ''Rising Icons''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Keri Hilson, The Dream and Idris Elba party with BET |publisher=S2Smagazine.com |url=http://www.s2smagazine.com/node/1381 |date=29 July 2009 |accessdate=29 July 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110724161300/http://www.s2smagazine.com/node/1381 |archivedate=24 July 2011 }}</ref> Elba announced the release of his first single \"Please Be True.\"<ref name=\"Jamaica Gleaner\">{{cite web|first=Davina |last=Morris |date=5 July 2009 |url=http://www.jamaica-gleaner.com/gleaner/20090705/ent/ent5.html |title=Man of many talents \u2013 Actor Idris Elba returns to his first love, music, with the release of his new single |work=Jamaica Gleaner |accessdate=29 July 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090816085502/http://www.jamaica-gleaner.com/gleaner/20090705/ent/ent5.html |archivedate=16 August 2009 }}</ref> In the August 2009 issue of ''[[Essence (magazine)|Essence]]'' magazine, he announced the name of his six-song EP as ''Kings Among Kings''.<ref name=\"Essence\">{{cite web|first=Jeannine |last=Amber |date=13 July 2009 |url=http://www.essence.com/news_entertainment/entertainment/articles/idris_elba_covers_essence |title=ESSENCE August Issue: Sexy Talk With Idris Elba |work=Essence |accessdate=14 August 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090817203109/http://www.essence.com/news_entertainment/entertainment/articles/idris_elba_covers_essence |archivedate=17 August 2009 }}</ref> He released his EP ''High Class Problems Vol. 1'' in the United Kingdom in February 2010, for which he has won many prizes including a ''Billboard'' Music Awards nomination.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://driis.com/blog/2010/02/08/high-class-problems-available-today|title=High Class Problems \u2013 Available Today!!!|publisher=driis|date=8 February 2010|accessdate=28 December 2011|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120314134843/http://driis.com/blog/2010/02/08/high-class-problems-available-today/|archivedate=14 March 2012}}</ref>\n\nIn 2011, he performed on the intro to [[Pharoahe Monch]]'s album ''[[W.A.R. (We Are Renegades)|W.A.R.]]''. The following year, he co-directed and performed in the [[Mumford & Sons]] music video for \"[[Lover of the Light]]\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1697394/mumford-and-sons-lover-of-the-light-music-video.jhtml|title=Mumford & Sons Only 'Think' They Understand 'Lover Of The Light' Video|publisher=}}</ref>\n\nIn 2014, he produced [[K. Michelle]]'s \"The Rebellious Soul Musical\" which debuted on [[VH1]] on 19 August 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://theurbandaily.com/2014/02/03/k-michelle-in-idris-elba-directed-musical/ |title=K. Michelle To Star In Idris Elba Directed Musical |publisher=The Urban Daily |date=3 February 2014 |accessdate=28 January 2015}}</ref> In May, Elba featured on [[Mr Hudson]]'s single \"Step Into the Shadows\". Mr Hudson also produced his album ''Idris Elba Presents mi Mandela'', which was released in November 2014.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/music/rockandpopfeatures/11238137/Idris-Elba-Presents-Mi-Mandela-album-stream3.html|title=Idris Elba Presents Mi Mandela: album stream|date=18 November 2014|publisher=|last1=Morgan|first1=Clive}}</ref><ref>Andy Gill, [https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/reviews/idris-elba-presents-mi-mandela-album-review-a-marvellous-alliance-of-ancient-and-modern-styles-9874681.html \"Idris Elba Presents mi Mandela, album review: A marvellous alliance of ancient and modern styles\"], ''The Independent'', 21 November 2014.</ref> He also featured on the remix of Ghanaian music group, VVIP's single \"Selfie\" together with Nigerian rapper [[Phyno]] released on 12 September 2014 and video released on YouTube on 11 April 2015.\n\nElba performed a rap for the second album by [[Noel Fielding]] and [[Sergio Pizzorno]]'s band, the [[Loose Tapestries]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nme.com/news/kasabian/78731|title=Kasabian's Serge Pizzorno and comedian Noel Fielding tease 'Wu-Tang Clan' live shows|accessdate=15 September 2014}}</ref> Elba also rapped in a remix of [[Skepta]]'s \"Shutdown\" which was uploaded on 1 June 2015 to SoundCloud.<ref>{{cite magazine|title=Idris Elba Raps About His 'Wire' Character in Skepta's 'Shutdown' Remix|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/the-juice/6583367/idris-elba-raps-about-his-wire-character-in-skeptas-shutdown|magazine=Billboard|date=27 October 2017}}</ref> On 17 August, a song was released on which Elba appeared on Nigerian singer [[D'banj]]'s single \"Confidential\", featuring Sierra Leonean rapper Shadow Boxer with the video uploaded to YouTube on 20 August. In November 2015, Elba opened for [[Madonna (entertainer)|Madonna]] during her [[Rebel Heart Tour]] in Berlin, Germany. Elba is also featured on the [[Macklemore & Ryan Lewis]] album ''[[This Unruly Mess I've Made]]'' (2016).\n\nIn July 2018, he launched his record label, 7Wallace Music.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Stutz |first1=Colin |title=Idris Elba Launches New Record Label 7Wallace Music, Announces French Artist James BKS as First Signing |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8463870/idris-elba-launches-new-record-label-7wallace-music-announces-french-artist |accessdate=10 February 2019 |agency=Billboard |date=3 July 2018}}</ref> Elba performed at [[Coachella Valley Music and Arts Festival]] in April 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/news/coachella-announces-2019-lineup-one-artist-at-a-time/ |title=Coachella 2019: Full Lineup Announced |website=Pitchfork |date=2 January 2019 |accessdate=3 January 2019}}</ref> In 2019 he featured on the track \u201c[[Boasty]]\u201d by British [[Grime (music genre)|grime]] artist [[Wiley (musician)|Wiley]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thefader.com/2019/03/07/wiley-stefflon-don-sean-paul-idris-elba-boasty|title=Sean Paul, Idris Elba, Stefflon Don, and 'Wiley' link-up in their 'Boasty' video|website=[[The Fader]]|last=Renshaw|first=David|date=7 March 2019|accessdate=17 July 2019}}</ref> Elba also appears in the \u201cBoasty\u201d music video, delivering his verse in a mansion that includes a film set.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://hypebeast.com/2019/3/wiley-stefflon-don-sean-paul-idris-elba-boasty-stream|title=Wiley Releases Music Video for \"Boasty\" Featuring Idris Elba, Sean Paul & Stefflon Don|website=Hypebeast|last=Brain|first=Eric|date=7 March 2019|accessdate=17 July 2019}}</ref> In 2019, Elba appears in [[Taylor Swift]]\u2019s song \"London Boy\" from her seventh studio album ''[[Lover (album)|Lover]]''. The intro of the song samples a snippet from an interview by Elba.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2019/music/news/taylor-swift-lover-album-review-1203311445/|title=Album Review: Taylor Swift's 'Lover'|last=Willman|first=Chris|last2=Willman|first2=Chris|date=23 August 2019|website=Variety|language=en|access-date=25 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Other work==\n[[File:Secretary of State Justine and actor Idris Elba (15395070906).jpg|thumb|Elba and British cabinet minister [[Justine Greening]] at a meeting with diaspora representatives at the 'Defeating Ebola in Sierra Leone' conference in London, October 2014]]\nIn October 2014, Elba presented the series ''Journey Dot Africa with Idris Elba'' on [[BBC Radio 2]], exploring all types of [[African music]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b04k6c9g |title=Journey Dot Africa with Idris Elba |publisher=BBC Radio 2 |date=28 October 2014 |accessdate=28 January 2015}}</ref> Elba has also featured in various television commercials for [[Sky (United Kingdom)|Sky]] box-sets in 2013, 2014, 2015, 2016, and 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2014/nov/29/idris-elba-sky-advert|title=Idris Elba's new Sky advert: why can't he wink?|date=29 November 2014|work=Guardian|accessdate=2 September 2015}}</ref> Elba has collaborated with the UK Parliament in their efforts to eradicate [[Ebola]] from West Africa, working alongside the UK [[Secretary of State for International Development]] Justine Greening in 2014. Elba has created a collaboration with British fashion label [[SuperGroup|Superdry]], which launched at the end of November 2015.<ref>{{cite web|title = Idris Elba's collaboration with Superdry puts the \"luxe\" in \"sports luxe\"|url = http://www.gq-magazine.co.uk/style/articles/2015-06/30/idris-elba-superdry-menswear-collection-launch-date-pictures-prices|website = GQ|publisher = |accessdate =5 November 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2016, Elba addresssd the UK Parliament in regards to the concern of the lack of diversity on screen. Stating, 'Change is coming but it's taking its sweet time', he spoke about the lack of diversity regarding race, gender and sexuality.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.businessinsider.com/idris-elba-diversity-speech-2016-1|title=Actor Idris Elba addressed British Parliament about the need for diversity on screen: 'Change is coming, but it's taking its sweet time'|last=Guerrasio|first=Jason|website=Business Insider|access-date=11 December 2019}}</ref>\n\nElba hosted [[The Best FIFA Football Awards 2017]] at the [[London Palladium]] on 23 October 2017. During the show he took a selfie of \"the best team in the world\" which included [[Lionel Messi]], [[Cristiano Ronaldo]] and [[Neymar]].<ref>{{cite news|title=The Best selfie: Idris Elba revels as host of Fifa Awards show|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2017/10/24/best-selfie-idris-elba-revels-host-fifa-awards-show/|work=The Daily Telegraph|date=27 October 2017}}</ref>\n\nHe had the idea to develop the music from his album ''Idris Elba Presents mi Mandela'' into a show, which ultimately resulted in a play called ''Tree'' which premiered at the [[Manchester International Festival]] in 2019.<ref name=\"bbctree\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-48887673|title=Can Idris Elba turn an album into a play? \u2605\u2605\u2605\u2606\u2606|work=BBC News|date=6 July 2019|via=www.bbc.co.uk}}</ref> However, authorship of the piece was disputed. On 2 July 2019, ''[[The Guardian]]'' published a story describing how writers Tori Allen-Martin and Sarah Henley claimed to have been removed from the production under what they described as questionable circumstances.<ref>Mark Brown, [https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2019/jul/02/writers-claim-being-excluded-after-creating-idris-elbas-play Writers claim being excluded after creating Idris Elba's play], ''[[The Guardian]]'', 2 July 2019.</ref> The two writers had worked on the project for four years following an approach from Elba asking them to develop his idea for a musical based on the album, on which Allen-Martin had also collaborated. [[Kwame Kwei-Armah]] joined the project in May 2018 and rewrote part of their material. At the time of its premiere ''Tree'' was billed as \"created by Idris Elba and Kwame Kwei-Armah\".<ref>{{cite web| url=https://mif.co.uk/whats-on/tree/|title=TREE|website=mif.co.uk|accessdate=3 July 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"bbctree\" /> Allen-Martin and Henley described their creative input as having included research and script-writing, as well as coming up with the play's title, and that after being removed they were threatened with legal action if they went public with the story.<ref>Tori Allen-Martin and Sarah Henley, [https://medium.com/@toriandsarahburnbright/tree-a-story-of-gender-and-power-in-theatre-23b8a2468224 Tree. A Story of Gender and Power in Theatre], blog post, 2 July 2019.</ref> Elba and Kwei-Armah both published rebuttals of the writers' account of what happened on Twitter.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-48843348|title=Dispute over Elba play Tree as writers claim they were 'pushed off'|website=bbc.co.uk|date=2 July 2019|accessdate=3 July 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Kickboxing career==\nDiscovery Channel produced a documentary, ''Idris Elba: Fighter'', chronicling Elba's 12-month [[kickboxing]] and [[mixed martial arts]] training<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/tv/2016/08/24/idris-elba-is-becoming-a-kickboxer-and-theres-a-documentary-to-p/ |title=Idris Elba is becoming a kickboxer, and there's a documentary to prove it |last=Vincent |first=Alice |date=24 August 2016 |newspaper=The Telegraph |publisher=The Telegraph |accessdate=12 February 2017}}</ref> under [[Muay Thai]] coach Kieran Keddle,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://fightland.vice.com/blog/an-interview-with-idris-elbas-kickboxing-coach |title=An Interview With Idris Elba's Kickboxing Coach |last=Kurchak |first=Sarah |date=2 September 2016 |website=Vice Fightland |publisher=Vice|accessdate=12 February 2017}}</ref> culminating in Elba's first professional kickboxing fight\u2013and win\u2013against Lionel Graves, a younger, more experienced Dutch opponent, at London's [[York Hall]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://entertainment.inquirer.net/205632/watch-actor-idris-elba-wins-kickboxing-match-at-age-44 |title=WATCH: Actor Idris Elba wins kickboxing match at age 44 |last=Ibarrola |first=Khristian |date=3 November 2016 |website=Inquirer.net |publisher=Philippine Daily Inquirer |accessdate=12 February 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/3am/celebrity-news/idris-elba-new-kickboxing-role-9613465 |title=Idris Elba on new kickboxing role: When I fought I'd hear my mum saying 'Don't let him kick you in the head' |last=Corcoran|first=Rachel |date=12 January 2017|website=Mirror.co.uk|publisher=Mirror |accessdate=19 February 2017}}</ref>\n\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Kickboxing record\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|- align=\"center\"\n| '''Date''' || '''Result''' || '''Opponent''' || '''Event''' || '''Location''' || '''Method''' || '''Round''' || '''Time''' || '''Record'''\n|-\n|- align=\"center\"\n| 28 August 2016 || {{yes2|'''Win'''}} ||align=left|{{flagicon|NED}} Lionel Graves || [[Glory (kickboxing)|Road to Glory UK]] || [[London|London, United Kingdom]] || TKO || 1 || N/A || 1\u20130\n|-\n|}\n'''''Legend''''': {{legend2|#CCFFCC|'''Win'''|border=1px solid #CCFFCC}}\n{{legend2|#FFBBBB|Loss |border=1px solid #FFBBBB}}\n{{legend2|#c5d2ea|Draw/No contest |border=1px solid #c5d2ea}}\n{{legend2|White|Notes |border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n|-\n|}\n\n==Personal life==\nElba has been married three times: first to Hanne \"Kim\" N\u00f8rgaard (from 1999 to 2003) and then to Sonya Nicole Hamlin (for four months in 2006). He has two children: a daughter with Kim named Isan (born 2002), who resides with N\u00f8rgaard in [[Atlanta, Georgia]],<ref>{{cite news|title=Idris Elba 'splits with long-term girlfriend Naiyana Garth|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/celebritynews/12149470/Idris-Elba-splits-with-long-term-girlfriend-Naiyana-Garth.html|work=The Daily Telegraph}}</ref> and a son named Winston (born 2014) with ex-girlfriend Naiyana Garth.<ref>{{cite news|last=Webber |first=Stephanie |url=http://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-moms/news/idris-elba-welcomes-baby-boy-winston-with-naiyana-garth-first-picture-2014184 |title=Idris Elba Welcomes Baby Boy Winston With Naiyana Garth: First Picture |work=[[Us Weekly]] |date=18 April 2014 |accessdate=28 January 2015}}</ref>  Elba became engaged to the [[Somali-Canadian]] Sabrina Dhowre on 10 February 2018, during a screening of his film ''[[Yardie (film)|Yardie]]'' at an [[East London]] cinema;<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/newsbeat-43024140 |title=Yardie actor on Idris Elba proposal: I had tears in my eyes |last=Moore |first=Hannah |date=11 February 2018 |work=BBC News |accessdate=11 February 2018}}</ref> the pair have been dating since early 2017.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/av/entertainment-arts-43019334/idris-elba-s-surprise-marriage-proposal |title=Idris Elba's surprise marriage proposal |date=10 February 2018 |work=BBC News |accessdate=11 February 2018}}</ref> They married on 26 April 2019, in [[Marrakesh]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/3am/celebrity-news/breaking-idris-elba-marries-sabrina-14780582|title=Idris Elba marries Sabrina Dhowre in secret ceremony|first=Emmeline|last=Saunders|date=27 April 2019|website=mirror}}</ref>\n\nElba states that he is [[spiritual but not religious]].<ref>{{cite web |url= http://cinema.com/articles/4812/reaping-the-idris-elba-qa.phtml |title=The Reaping: Idris Elba Q&A |website=cinema.com |year=2015 |accessdate=28 January 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.craveonline.com/film/articles/157684-idris-elba-international-man |title=Idris Elba: International Man |first=Fred |last=Topel |website=CraveOnline |date=30 November 1999 |accessdate=28 January 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150114081440/http://www.craveonline.com/film/articles/157684-idris-elba-international-man |archivedate=14 January 2015 }}</ref> Elba is an avid supporter of [[Arsenal F.C]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Arsenal fan Idris Elba: I would be physically sick if Tottenham won the Premier League title|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/arsenal-fan-idris-elba-i-would-be-physically-sick-if-tottenham-won-premier-league-title-a3226766.html|work=London Evening Standard|date=27 October 2017}}</ref> In 2015, as part of his [[Discovery Channel]] miniseries ''Idris Elba: No Limits'', Elba broke the course record [[British land speed record|land speed]] \"Flying Mile\" for the [[Pendine Sands]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Actor Idris Elba Breaks Historic 'Flying Mile' Record in Bentley|website= Bentley Media|date= 7 May 2015 |url=http://www.bentleymedia.com/release/638 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20150509214539/http://www.bentleymedia.com/release/638|accessdate=9 May 2015 |archive-date= 9 May 2015}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Prince's Trust]], a UK youth charity founded by [[Charles, Prince of Wales|Prince Charles]] in 1976, which Elba credits with helping to start his career, appointed him as their anti-crime ambassador in April 2009.<ref>{{cite web|title=Idris Elba Becomes Anti Crime Ambassador|website=Looktothestars.com|date=8 April 2009|url=http://www.looktothestars.org/news/2332-idris-elba-becomes-anit-crime-ambassador|accessdate=11 April 2009}}</ref> Elba voiced support for a vote to remain in the [[European Union]] for the [[2016 United Kingdom European Union membership referendum]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/eu-referendum-brexit-remain-who-do-celebrities-support-david-beckham-jk-rowling-a7094751.html|title=The celebrities that support Brexit (and the ones backing Remain)|work=The Independent|accessdate=27 November 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Idris Elba announces his support for the UK to remain in the EU |url=https://filmindustry.network/idris-elba-announces-support-uk-remain-europe/31366 |publisher=Film Industry Network |date=15 June 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn 16 March 2020, Elba announced that he had been diagnosed with [[COVID-19]] amidst the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus: Idris Elba confirms he has tested positive for COVID-19 |url=https://news.sky.com/story/coronavirus-idris-elba-confirms-he-has-tested-positive-for-covid-19-11958621 |accessdate=16 March 2020 |work=Sky News |date=16 March 2020}}</ref> His wife, Sabrina Dhowre Elba, also tested positive for the disease.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/03/22/entertainment/sabrina-dhowre-idris-elba-coronavirus/index.html|title=Idris Elba's wife, Sabrina Dhowre, also tests positive for coronavirus|first=Lisa Respers |last=France|website=CNN|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref> During his quarantine period, he noted that he has been suffering from [[asthma]] all his life, placing him in the high risk category of the disease.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/idriselba/status/1239997526268207105|title=Periscope stream|first=Idris|last=Elba|date=17 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 31 March 2020, Idris Elba has announced both he and his wife Sabrina, 30, have passed the two-week quarantine period after being tested positive for coronavirus. \n\nThe actor, 47, took to Twitter on Tuesday evening to share a health update where he told fans they were 'doing ok' and still asymptomatic. \n\nIdris, who has been in quarantine in New Mexico after he discovered he had COVID-19 while shooting his new Netflix film, said they are 'stuck in limbo' because they can't get a flight back to the U.K.\n\n==Awards and honours==\n{{main|List of awards and nominations received by Idris Elba}}\nIn May 2007, Elba was selected as one of ''[[People (magazine)|People]]''{{'}}s annual 100 Most Beautiful People in the World.<ref>{{cite news |title=''People'' Magazine's 'Most Beautiful People' issue |work=[[CBS News]] |url=http://www.cbsnews.com/htdocs/pdf/042507_people_list_facts.pdf |accessdate=11 April 2009}}</ref> In 2013, he was named ''Essence''{{'}}s annual  Sexiest Man of the Year<ref>{{cite news |first=Charli |last=Penn |url=http://photos.essence.com/galleries/essences-2013-sexiest-man-year-50-reasons-love-idris-elba/ |title=''ESSENCE''{{'}}s 2013 Sexiest Man of the Year: 50 Reasons to Love Idris Elba |magazine=[[Essence (magazine)|Essence]] |date=9 December 2013 |accessdate=28 January 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150114072621/http://photos.essence.com/galleries/essences-2013-sexiest-man-year-50-reasons-love-idris-elba/ |archive-date=14 January 2015 |url-status=dead }}</ref> and was ranked No. 2 in ''People''{{'}}s annual Sexiest Man Alive.<ref>{{cite news |last=Hogan |first=Kate |url=https://people.com/celebrity/sexiest-man-alive-2013-adam-levine-david-beckham-brad-pitt-idris-elba/ |title=Sexiest Man Alive 2013: Adam Levine, David Beckham, Brad Pitt, Idris Elba |magazine=[[People (magazine)|People]] |date=20 November 2013 |accessdate=7 November 2018}}</ref> In October 2014, Elba was presented with a [[MOBO Awards|MOBO Inspiration Award]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Mobo Awards 2014: Idris Elba receives inspiration award |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/culturevideo/musicvideo/11116450/Mobo-Awards-2014-Idris-Elba-receives-inspiration-award.html |newspaper=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |date=23 September 2014 |accessdate=7 November 2018 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180109153226/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/culturevideo/musicvideo/11116450/Mobo-Awards-2014-Idris-Elba-receives-inspiration-award.html |archivedate=9 January 2018 }}</ref>\n\nIn 2015, he was named one of ''[[GQ]]'' magazine's 50 best-dressed British men.<ref>{{cite news|title=50 Best Dressed Men in Britain 2015 |last=Johnston |first=Robert |url=http://www.gq-magazine.co.uk/style/articles/2015-01/05/best-dressed-men-2015/ |magazine=[[GQ]] |date=5 January 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150107145128/http://www.gq-magazine.co.uk/style/articles/2015-01/05/best-dressed-men-2015 |archivedate=7 January 2015 }}</ref> Elba was appointed an Officer of the [[Order of the British Empire]] (OBE) in the [[2016 New Year Honours]] for services to drama.<ref>{{London Gazette |issue=61450 |supp=y |page=N12 |date=30 December 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Mendick |first1=Robert |last2=Swinford |first2=Steven |title=New Year's Honours: Idris Elba, Barbara Windsor, Damon Albarn and Ronnie O'Sullivan named in 2016 list |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/honours-list/12075218/New-Years-Honours-Idris-Elba-Barbara-Windsor-Damon-Albarn-and-Ronnie-OSullivan-named-in-2016-list.html |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph |date=31 December 2015 |accessdate=31 December 2015}}</ref> In 2017, Elba won the male title for the \"[[Rear of the Year]]\" award in Britain.<ref>{{cite news |last=Adetula |first=Elizabeth |title=Idris Elba's bum wins Rear Of The Year because he's got buns, hun |url=http://metro.co.uk/2017/07/25/idris-elbas-bum-wins-rear-of-the-year-because-hes-got-buns-hun-6802970/ |newspaper=[[Metro (British newspaper)|Metro]] |date=25 July 2017|accessdate=30 December 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2018, he was one of 50 people named for \"making London awesome\" and helping to shape London's cultural landscape who were featured in ''[[Time Out (magazine)|Time Out]]'' to mark the magazine's 50th anniversary.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Kheraj |first=Alim |last2=''Time Out'' editors |url=https://www.timeout.com/london/things-to-do/50-londoners-who-make-the-city-awesome |title=50 Londoners who make the city awesome |magazine=[[Time Out (magazine)|Time Out]] |date=14 September 2018 |accessdate=7 November 2018}}</ref> On 5 November 2018, it was announced he had been named ''People''{{'}}s Sexiest Man alive via ''[[The Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon]]''.<ref>{{cite news |first=Julie |last=Jordan |title=Idris Elba Is PEOPLE's Sexiest Man Alive 2018: It's 'an Ego Boost for Sure' |url=https://people.com/movies/idris-elba-sexiest-man-alive-2018-reveal/ |magazine=People |date=6 November 2018 |accessdate=7 November 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n{{main|Idris Elba filmography}}\n\n==Discography==\n'''Albums'''\n* 2015: ''Murdah Loves John (The John Luther Character Album)''\n\n'''Extended plays'''\n* 2006: ''Big Man''\n* 2009: ''Kings Among Kings''\n* 2010